These are AMAZING rifles but they are just a bit to heavy for my wife, so I'm going a different way for her and have also decided to build something else special/custom for myself. My lose your gain of a sweet rifle!

They have the fallowing:
- CNC Billet recievers
- Nickel Boron coated Bolt Carrier groups
- 1-8 twist, .223 Wyled chambers (take both 5.56 & .223 but more accurate) 16"" Stainless     Steel, fluted barrel
- 7"" super light quadrail
- KNS Anti walk trigger pins
- Magpul MOE grip & Stock
- Magpul ASAP Sling mount
- Oversize charging handle latch
- Black Rain's signature crazy looking Pineapple muzzle
These are expensive rifles, as seen here, http://www.blackrainordnance.com/bro-pg5/
(mine don't have the new model BRO DIT trigger or Adjustable gas block that is shown here)
I'm letting them go cheap hoping to get on to my new projects soon ;)
$1,200 each
Call
(FIVE 73) FIVE 52- 724Eight

35,http://www.armslist.com/posts/3661035,"For Sale:  FN M16a2 w/PSA custom lower, Viet Nam A1 stock, magazine -SOLD","Redmond, Snoqualmie, sometimes Gig Harbor, Seattle, Washington",$ 950,"Listed On: Friday, October 31, 2014",Rifles,FN Herstal S.A.                                                                                ,223/5.56 NATO                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"-SOLD- This is an ex-military complete FN m16a2 upper from the Indiana National Guard.  It was racked and never issued, the gun later converted to M4 and the upper surplussed.  It is complete all the way through with the correct A.O. Toolcraft bcg, FN chromed-lined, hammer forged 1/9 barrel, etc.   It has rack wear but it barely used and perhaps not fired other than initial testing.

It has a PSA lower that has been modified to give a partial-fence early A1 lower look, and PSA logo and model removed (legal information - maker, location, s/n remain of course).  It has been refinished in Dark Parkerizing grey and is close to the Colt M-16 grey.  AR fire control group, of course.  The lower was given some after-finish aging to give an early Viet Nam era look.  The furniture is an early-vietnam era M16a1 stock that has been carefully refinished and in excellent condition.  The magazine is a Viet Nam era Simmonds 20rd. with original finish.  The USAF actually issued guns like this - updates of their earlier XM16e1 models updated with an A2 upper.  So that was the theme.
Hate to sell but need the money.  Can ship in-state if needed, otherwise ftf with 18+ year old non-felonious WA resident.
SOLD"

History of the Beretta 92FS

Designed in 1975 by Carlo Beretta, Giuseppe Mazzetti, and Vittorio Valle; the Beretta 92 (made in Italy) pistol is an evolution from the M1922 and M1951. Taking the open slide design from the M1922 and its alloy frame and locking barrel from the M1951. Along the way the Beretta 92 also adopted a direct feed and a ""double-stacked"" high capacity design to its magazine.

In order to meet the requirements of select law enforcement agencies, Beretta added a slide-mounted combined safety and docking lever. Thus the Beretta 92S was born and adopted by several Italian law enforcement and military units.

Eventually Beretta modified the 92SB (a special model with a firing pin block designed for the U.S. Air Force) with an enlarged hammer pin to stop the slide from flying off the frame in response to reports of defective slides during U.S. Military testing."
